
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Research Project Management System

class Department {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class ResearchGroup {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -department: Department
}

class Researcher {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -currentResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

class WorkPackage {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -project: Project
  -leadingResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Assignment {
  -id: int
  -researcher: Researcher
  -workPackage: WorkPackage
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -createdBy: ResearchGroup
}

' Relationships
Department "1" --> "0..*" ResearchGroup : contains
ResearchGroup "1" --> "0..*" Researcher : contains
Project "1" --> "0..*" WorkPackage : contains
WorkPackage "1" --> "1" ResearchGroup : led by
Researcher "0..*" --> "0..*" Assignment : assigned to
WorkPackage "0..*" --> "0..*" Assignment : has team members

' Note about service delivery traceability
note right of Assignment
  Service delivery is tracked via this assignment.
  When researcher changes group or WP leadership changes,
  assignments are terminated and re-created.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Department**: A department can contain many research groups.
- **ResearchGroup**: Belongs to one department and contains researchers.
- **Researcher**: Belongs to exactly one research group at any time.
- **Project**: Contains multiple work packages.
- **WorkPackage**: Part of a project and led by one research group.
- **Assignment**: Links a researcher to a work package, with dates and tracking of which group created the assignment (i.e., who "delivered" the service).

This model ensures that even if a researcher moves groups or the leadership of a WP changes, the historical record of service delivery is preserved in the `Assignment` class.